What follows is an explanation of why the odds favor Trump, and what eight years of his leadership would mean for global security.
The point is that, Robert Mueller and Kamala Harris notwithstanding, President Trump is probably going to be reelected.
So what does that mean for global security?
However, there is one critical consequence for global security that you can take to the bank if he wins reelection.
That global order was grounded in three fundamental precepts: support for democratic principles, collective security against Russian aggression, and liberalization of international trade.